      "@coffeemug Do you have an opinion on whether to include garbage collection?\r\n\r\nOne concern is that if you have a steady write workload, there might always be some GCing going on in the background. As a consequence you would see a garbage collection entry with a very long duration. This might confuse users who wonder why it's not finishing.\r\nI wonder if giving the garbage collection job a slightly different name such as `incremental_gc` or `background_gc` could avoid some of that confusion.\r\n\r\nOn the other side there's what @AtnNn and I said about disk i/o."
